The paper deals with the problem of reconstructing HDR images from a single exposure using deep learning algorithms. This involves image processing, computer vision, and machine learning techniques, which are all covered by the computer vision (cs.CV) and graphics (cs.GR) sub-categories. The paper also mentions the use of simulated datasets and pre-training, which are common techniques in multimedia (cs.MM) and machine learning (cs.LG) research. Finally, the paper proposes a deep convolutional neural network (CNN), which is a popular type of deep learning algorithm used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) research.
